net.trevize.labelme.lucene
Class LuceneLabelMeDocument

java.lang.Object
  net.trevize.labelme.lucene.LuceneLabelMeDocument

public class LuceneLabelMeDocument
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides a static method for creating Lucene Document for indexing. These documents are filled with some fields for an image depicted with the LabelThem.xsd XML Schema. Using the fields: 1. filenames (image and annotation), 2. folder (image and annotation), 3. object name (multiple fields in each Lucene Document). TODO: - adding more fields from the LabelMe dataset (polygon, etc.), it could be very useful for example for querying with a sketch for locating named objects in images.

Author:
Nicolas James [[http://njames.trevize.net]] LabelMeDocument.java - May 20, 2009
